{
  "stem": "27509.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she, if I got into trouble with Father, she would defend me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She would stand [INAUDIBLE] to take my side, as any mother would do, and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was a very lovely and very, very warm and cordial relationship, insofar-- and again, insofar that it was socially permissible to express these relations, even between parents and children.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It had to be at a safe distance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, sure-- my-- next to me was my sister Shifra.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was-- she was born two years [? after ?] [? me, ?] in '21.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That-- then was a brother, by the name Hershl, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] born two years after that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then was a brother, by the name Lazar, born in '25.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the youngest, Simcha or Sam, as we know him here, born in '27.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All of them survived the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My parents and the five-- and the four children survived the war by the-- by the good grace of the Russian authorities send them to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Otherwise, they would have not survived it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, with my sister, I was at school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I lost a year coming from the other, lower schools.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I had to be in the same class with her, which was a bit-- in fact, I was in the same class with her and with my cousin, my uncle's only daughter.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there were three Kipens in the same class.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- [COUGHS] but of course, being a girl and the only girl among four brothers, she held out a position of-- of separate identity and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The younger brothers, of course, were already a bit too young when I was-- when I was a boy of 14, 15, they were still young children.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
